cscie55.project.commands

Enum Commands

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Commands>
      • cscie55.project.commands.Commands
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Commands>

    public enum Commands
extends java.lang.Enum<Commands>
    Enumeration containing the possible commands between the ATM clients and a server.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DEPOSIT
      Command to indicate the deposit of an amount of money into a client's account.
      DONE
      Command from a client to indicate to the server that it has finished attending its transactions.
      EXIT
      Command to indicate to the server that it has finished attending all transactions.
      INQUIRE
      Command to indicate the query of the balance of a client's account.
      START
      Command to indicate the beginning of a transaction between a client and the server.
      TRANSFER
      Command to indicate the transfer of money from one account to another.
      WITHDRAW
      Command to indicate the withdrawal of an amount of money into a client's account.
